 Selected slice: 006X7-credit-object-scope-action-parity-closure
 
-The selected agent must replace this template with a slice-specific execution plan before editing product code.
+1. Characterize the existing 006X6 public action/write matrix and its shared action evaluators,
+   HTTP object-denial behavior, and full evidence snapshot helpers.
+2. RED: replace static object-scope inventory credit with executable case registration and add one
+   tracer case that evaluates the persisted resource after scope is removed; save the false-
+   completeness and disabled-projection failures under `evidence/terminal-logs/`.
+3. GREEN in vertical cycles: make eligibility, loan-limit, appraisal create/update/revalidate/
+   submit-review/review, and sanction object-scope cases evaluate an exact disabled six-field action,
+   invoke the matching public write, compare stable reason/error category, and preserve the complete
+   evidence snapshot. Keep HTTP detail/write non-disclosure at standard 403 envelopes.
+4. Run the focused matrix and endpoint regressions, generate a reviewable object-denial/evidence
